          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690290203861-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690290203861-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690290203861-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the tomatoes are softening, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong> in 450ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[900ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml]</span><strong> milk</strong> – this is your <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach </strong>and pat dry with kitchen paper </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690290207779-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690290207779-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690290207779-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690290207779-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690290207779-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> stock</strong> to a medium-sized pot (with a matching lid) with the <strong>orzo</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 12-15 min or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690290211398-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690290211398-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
